Package se.arkalix.core.plugin.eh

Interface EventSubscriptionRequest

  • public interface EventSubscriptionRequest
    A request for some subscriber to receive events matching certain topic and metadata requirements.

    • Method Summary

        java.lang.String topic()

      • subscriber

      • metadata

        java.util.Map<java.lang.String,​java.lang.String> metadata()
        Metadata key/value pairs that must exist in each EventOutgoing matched by this subscription.

      • sendToUri

        java.lang.String sendToUri()
        The URI to which matching events will be sent as an HTTP POST request.

        In other words, whenever an eligible EventIncoming becomes available to the Event Handler receiving this subscription, the subscriber will be sent an HTTP POST message with this URI, containing the matching EventIncoming as message body.

      • useMetadata

        boolean useMetadata()
        true only if the metadata map is to be used when deciding what events to forward to the subscriber.

      • startsAt

        java.util.Optional<java.lang.String> startsAt()
        The instant at which this subscription starts to be applied, unless as soon as possible.
        See Also:
        Instants.fromAitiaDateTimeString(String)

      • stopsAt

        java.util.Optional<java.lang.String> stopsAt()
        The instant at which this subscription is terminated, if ever.
        See Also:
        Instants.fromAitiaDateTimeString(String)

      • publishers

        java.util.List<SystemDetails> publishers()
        The systems from which events are to be received.

        If no publishers are specified at all, this list will be treated as if containing all possible publishers.
